data.COLLECTION_LOCATION: United Kingdom | Argyllshire | Benmore Botanic Garden | Mixed conifer arboretum in mesic floodplain.
data.HABITAT: rotted conifer stump in mesic arboretum
data.DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Collected live into paper packets into the field. Air dried, cleaned of bryophytes and subsampled back at the lab .
data.OTHER_INFORMATION: Fungal R&D Panel. Cladonia grow as stalks (podetia) with tiny leaves. There are many separate stalks with tiny leaves, all from the same mat, in this sample. The stalks are likely, but not certain to represent single individuals, but even stalks growing together may not be the same individual. Likewise, the tiny leaves may have separate origins that the stalks they arise from. All stalks in this sample are from the same small 'mat' of tightly packed stalks. Algal symbiont: Asterochloris sp. Other potential contaminants: green algal epiphytes
